The paper deals with properties of digraphs and their compositions, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of arc-disjoint in- and out-branchings is also related to network flow problems, which fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses algorithms for deciding whether a given digraph has a good pair rooted at a given vertex, which is a topic in computer science (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
